&quot;SO WHAT'S NEW&quot;:<br>
The poem is not anonymous...it's by Rudyard Kipling, writing<br>
of the British Army.<br><br>
All this talk about victimization and betrayal is incredibly foreign to me.  I gave the government an untried and unsophisticated youth, just 17.  In return they gave me a high school diploma, an undergraduate degree, a graduate degree, a commission, provided - and provided for - a spouse and six children, and experiences in all parts of the world - to include two tours in RVN, and a Purple Heart - that I wouldn't trade for anything, and don't have to, because I got it all for a measly 30 years of my life.  I guess it depends on what you want, and how you go about getting it.  I stumbled across this site entirely by accident, and I don't quite know what to make of it.  I was a professional soldier; I guess I'm an amateur veteran.  Rather have it that way, than the other way around.
